Name: moto
Description: The traditional cuisine of Japan (washoku) is based on rice with miso soup and other dishes. There is an emphasis on seasonal ingredients. Side dishes often consist of fish, pickled vegetables, and vegetables cooked in broth. Seafood is common, often grilled, but also served raw as sashimi or in sushi

Name: the keg steakhouse + bar
Description: Don’t worry if time is not on your side. We have carefully planned dishes that are light and delicious, and perfect for those quick lunch breaks. But we’re equally happy to help you while away the afternoon. Our full menu and wine list is always available when nothing but big steaks and big reds will do.

Name: agra indian cuisine
Description: AGRA is one of the most famous places in India. The alluring beauty of the Taj Mahal made AGRA a legend around the world. We have attempted to recreate and maintain the same ambiance, atmosphere and flavours that would make your visit a memorable one when you step in AGRA Fine Indian Cuisine.

Name: little sheep hotpot
Description: The best hot pot in Toronto is a perfect balance of fresh ingredients, delicious soups, and delectable dipping sauces. This classic Chinese comfort cuisine is perfect to warm you up as the temperature starts to cool down. Be it spicy, savoury, or lightly flavoured, the excellent varieties served up by local restaurants prove that there truly is a hot pot for everyone.
